se.jguru.nazgul.core.algorithms.event.api.consumer

Interface EventConsumer<E extends EventConsumer<E>>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The exact subtype of EventConsumer in effect.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Clusterable, Comparable<E>, EventListener, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEventConsumer

    public interface EventConsumer<E extends EventConsumer<E>>
extends EventListener, Comparable<E>, Clusterable
    EventConsumer/EventListener specification with callback methods invoked when events occur. EventConsumer instances should function correctly in a clustered environment, and must also be Comparable to enforce a natural ordering and comparison between instances.
    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB
